  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6595.87 sitting right between the massive negative gamma wall at 6590 (-15.2B) and positive gamma wall at 6605 (+17.9B), dealers are currently in buy-mode as spot trades above the max negative gamma strike, creating amplifying conditions in this tight 15-point range. The breakout regime with -7.1B total GEX means any directional move will be accelerated by dealer hedging, particularly if we break below 6590 where dealers will aggressively sell into weakness or above 6605 where they'll sell into strength. Watch for volatile whipsaws between these two massive gamma walls, with 6580 (-12.4B) providing additional downside amplification and 6600/6610 acting as resistance levels where dealers will fade rallies.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect violent swings between 6590-6605 with any break triggering fast moves in that direction.",
